    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "bff68afd-2755-4c81-a78f-ac9195bd5232",
    "name": "Why QMU?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Why QMU?",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>You will join our community of communications academics and practitioners and as a matriculated QMU student can access the University’s resources, including our extensive library and online teaching Hub.</li>\n<li>The block face-to-face teaching approach and online materials will help you combine studying with working.</li>\n<li>Our PR academics are recognised nationally and internationally for their excellence in research practice.</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "05a7efbd-9293-4763-9a83-dbc4c0dce1a7",
    "name": "Course overview",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Course overview",
    "content": "<p>Everyone enrolled on our Chartered Institute of Public Relations (CIPR) Diplomas is a matriculated student and has access to all of the University’s resources, including our extensive library and online teaching Hub. We very much believe that students gain real benefits from face-to-face teaching, but we also recognise that this can sometimes be difficult for professionals, so we organise our workshops on Fridays or Saturdays and always post material online.</p>\n<p>You will join our community of communications academics and practitioners, and will learn alongside our MSc students. Should you wish to continue studying with us after completing a diploma, you will have already earned 20 credits per CIPR Diploma module towards our <a data-udi=\"umb://document/eb1e207b75dd4dea9d3bf38c9d16f3e1\" href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/eb1e207b75dd4dea9d3bf38c9d16f3e1}\" title=\"MSc Digital Campaigning and Content Creation\">MSc Digital Campaigning and Content Creation</a> or <a data-udi=\"umb://document/54b1660569064b9cbcdb94a0216ddf28\" href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/54b1660569064b9cbcdb94a0216ddf28}\" title=\"MSc Strategic Communication and Public Relations (Mohawk College)\">MSc Strategic Communication and Public Relations</a>.</p>\n<p>Get ready to gain an advanced understanding of professional practice, including PR strategy and planning, content management, media and engagement, measurement and evaluation, and PR leadership, all underpinned by reference to ethics and the code of conduct. You’ll also put your learning into practice, evaluating a wide range of PR concepts and techniques and applying them practically to your own work and sector.</p>\n<p><a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://cipr.co.uk/CIPR/Learn_Develop/Qualifications/Specialist_Diploma__Public_Affairs.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">For more information, visit the CIPR website</a>. <a href=\"https://www.cipr.co.uk/content/qualifications/specialist-diploma-public-affairs\"></a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "2a3942fa-21f0-4499-a7e2-5ff627e4087c",
    "name": "Exit awards",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Exit awards",
    "content": "<p>Specialist Diploma (Public Affairs) plus 20 credits towards QMU’s <a data-id=\"12648\" href=\"/{localLink:12648}\" title=\"MSc Strategic Communication and Public Relations\">MSc Strategic Communication and Public Relations</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "1c0adbd2-4636-4766-ab6c-07ecd953d563",
    "name": "Structure",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Structure",
    "content": "<p>The diplomas are taught in blocks and you will only be required to attend QMU a few times across the duration of your chosen course. Each diploma usually consists of four full days or eight half days face-to-face teaching.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "28b79a4a-8387-4b04-8035-0cad5029166c",
    "name": "Teaching, learning and assessment",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching, learning and assessment",
    "content": "<p>You will be taught by our PR academics who are recognised nationally and internationally for their excellence in research. Your teaching will comprise a variety of approaches including lectures, workshops, group work and input from senior practitioners and QMU academics.</p>\n<p>Work is set at the on-campus teaching blocks and contact maintained between blocks through online discussions.</p>\n<p>You will learn alongside people who are working in a similar role to you in a variety of businesses and organisations as well as postgraduate students studying MScs. This will enable you to share experiences and learning with one another, which enriches the student experience.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "2f913aa0-5ea0-4efd-9b28-926a78c5c510",
    "name": "Teaching hours and attendance",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching hours and attendance",
    "content": "<p>Teaching on the Specialist Diploma (Public Affairs) is delivered in block teaching, in eight half days (and one full day).</p>\n<p>The timetable is not available at the time of posting.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "ec68f98b-9fe1-402d-bb4e-a7ee1600ccf5",
    "name": "Industry links and accreditation",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": " Industry links and accreditation",
    "content": "<p>QMU is an accredited teaching centre of the UK’s professional body, the Chartered Institute of Public Relations (CIPR) and a partner institution of the UK’s Public Relations Consultants Association.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "4befb0b1-18a6-4317-b9ed-e003f8fed3ed",
    "name": "Modules",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Modules",
    "content": "<p><a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://cipr.co.uk/CIPR/Learn_Develop/Qualifications/Specialist_Diploma__Public_Affairs.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">For the latest module information, please visit the diploma entry on the CIPR website.</a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "218370f8-c3e3-4556-aa14-ab5976c43fba",
    "name": "Class sizes",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Class sizes",
    "content": "<p>Normally, there are around 15-20 students on the module.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "3c9cb95e-b76e-4496-91d0-eb9f62c1d363",
    "name": "Entry requirements",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Entry requirements",
    "content": "<p><a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://cipr.co.uk/CIPR/Learn_Develop/Qualifications/Specialist_Diploma__Public_Affairs.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Please visit the CIPR website for the most up-to-date entry requirements. </a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "287f9b96-9759-4fb0-9f79-a9c3feec363d",
    "name": "Application deadline",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Application deadline",
    "content": "<p>None</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "268c32bd-cb6f-49d8-95d6-6ee71e87654a",
    "name": "More information and contacts",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "More information and contacts",
    "content": "<p><a href=\"mailto:%20mpieczka@qmu.ac.uk\">Contact Dr Magda Pieczka</a> or <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"mailto:admissions@qmu.ac.uk\" target=\"_blank\">contact Admissions</a> or <a href=\"https://cipr.co.uk/CIPR/Learn_Develop/Qualifications/Specialist_Diploma__Public_Affairs.aspx\">CIPR/Learn_Develop/Qualifications/Specialist_Diploma__Public_Affairs</a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "371c870b-350a-4df2-812f-1e2e69d55697",
    "name": "Opportunities to meet us",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Opportunities to meet us",
    "content": "<p><a href=\"/open-days-and-meeting-us/\">Click for information on our forthcoming open events</a></p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
